 **The four PEER roles** (`senior-developer`, `pair-programmer`, `tester`, `slacker`) act on `pause` / `resume` and **ignore `escalate`**:
 
 - On `payload.directive == "pause"`: **HALT all work immediately and ignore other nudges** until a matching resume arrives. Do not start, continue, or commit work while paused.
-  - **`kill_subagents` (optional pause field).** When the `pause` payload carries `kill_subagents: true` (an urgent stop — e.g. M's reaction to a `manager_monitor` `usage-limit`), then BEFORE halting, `TaskStop` every subagent + ephemeral work-Monitor you spawned **this session** — the token-burning work — and only then halt. To do this, each role keeps an **in-session list of the task IDs it spawned** (via the `Agent` tool or an ephemeral `Monitor`) and `TaskStop`s each one. **EXEMPT — never kill — your own bus-tail Monitor:** it is your *resume lifeline*. `resume` is broadcast on the bus; a peer that killed its bus-tail would be permanently deaf to `resume` (it could never hear the lift — human-only recovery), and bus-tail costs ~0 tokens while idle. So bus-tail stays listening through the pause; you do NOT re-arm it on resume because it was never killed. `kill_subagents` absent or false → today's behavior (halt, leave subagents running). The field is backward-compatible.
+  - **`kill_subagents` (optional pause field).** When the `pause` payload carries `kill_subagents: true` (an urgent stop — e.g. M's reaction to a `manager_monitor` `usage-limit`), then BEFORE halting, `TaskStop` every subagent + ephemeral work-Monitor you spawned **this session** — the token-burning work — and only then halt. To do this, each role keeps an **in-session list of the task IDs it spawned** (via the `Agent` tool or an ephemeral `Monitor`) and `TaskStop`s each one. (After killing the subagents, halt.) `resume` is broadcast on the bus; a peer that killed its bus-tail would be permanently deaf to `resume` (it could never hear the lift — human-only recovery), and bus-tail costs ~0 tokens while idle. So bus-tail stays listening through the pause; you do NOT re-arm it on resume because it was never killed. `kill_subagents` absent or false → today's behavior (halt, leave subagents running). The field is backward-compatible.
 - On `payload.directive == "resume"`: stop halting and continue normal work. (Your bus-tail — never killed — delivered this resume.)
 - On `payload.directive == "escalate"`: **IGNORE** — escalate is the manager's directive (the human-escalation channel), not a peer's (role-asymmetry).
 
